## [2026-04-28] ingest | 10.1016##J.JMB.2007.03.007 — Recombinant Rhodopsin N2C/D282C

- **Raw paper**: 10.1016/j.jmb.2007.03.007 — Crystal Structure of a Thermally Stable Rhodopsin Mutant
- **Key finding**: First structure of a recombinantly produced GPCR (COS-1 cells)
- **Updated page**: [[bovine-rhodopsin]] — Added Recombinant N2C/D282C section with full workflow:
  - COS-1 expression (~0.6 mg yield, 10% higher than native)
  - 1D4 immunoaffinity purification, Sephadex G50 detergent exchange (DDM → C8E4)
  - Crystallization: 1.2–1.7 M Li₂SO₄, 0.1 M Hepes pH 7.5, 0.05% LDAO, 10 mg/ml
  - Microcrystallography (5 µm beam, ESRF ID13), P3₁, 3.4 Å, PDB 2J4Y
  - Engineered C2-C282 disulfide: +10°C stability, fixes N-terminal cap
  - Triple mutant N2C/N15D/D282C (deglycosylated): did NOT improve crystal quality
- **Updated**: [[opsin-gpcr]] — Added DOI to sources; updated cross-reference description
- **Updated**: [[li2so4]] — Added DOI to sources; added bovine rhodopsin crystallization details (1.2–1.7 M)
- **Updated**: [[lDAO]] — Added DOI to sources; added recombinant bovine rhodopsin entry
- **checklist.csv**: Updated both DOIs (JMB.2004.08.090 and JMB.2007.03.007)

