## [2026-04-28] batch | 5 DOIs incorporated (DOI 6-10)

### DOI 6: 10.1016##J.MOLCEL.2011.10.020 — ICMT (Isoprenylcysteine Carboxyl Methyltransferase)
- **New page created**: [[icmt]] — Integral membrane SAM-dependent methyltransferase
  - *Methanosarcina acetivorans* ortholog (Ma-ICMT)
  - 5 TM helices + cytosolic C-terminal helix, 3.4 Å, PDB 4A2N
  - SAM cofactor pocket enclosed in catalytic subdomain, substrate access tunnel from membrane
  - Arg163 (M2 motif) positions substrate carboxylate for nucleophilic attack
  - Expression: E. coli C41(DE3), Ma-ICMT-GFP-His7, 20°C overnight
  - Purification: Ni-NTA → ion exchange → SEC
  - Detergent: 0.024% DDM
  - Crystallization: 8 mg/ml, 20 mM MES pH 6.5, 200 mM NaCl, 10% glycerol, 0.024% DDM, 5 mM SAH, 0.5 mg/ml polar lipids
  - SAD phasing: KAu(CN)2 or EMTS derivatives, Diamond I02/I03

### DOI 7: 10.1016##J.STR.2012.03.014 — β1-Adrenoceptor with Biased Agonists
- **New page created**: [[beta1ar-biased-agonists]] — Thermostabilized avian β1AR-m23 with bucindolol (3.2 Å) and carvedilol (2.3 Å)
  - PDB 4AMI (bucindolol), 4AMJ (carvedilol), P2₁ space group
  - Biased agonism: both stimulate G protein-independent pathways while acting as inverse/partial agonists of G protein pathway
  - Bucindolol and carvedilol interact with additional residues in EL2 and TM7
  - Ser215⁵,⁴⁶ forms interhelical H-bond (partial agonist-like); no binding pocket contraction
  - H8-H1 interface: Arg355⁸,⁵⁶ H-bonds with Ser68¹,⁵⁹/Thr69¹,⁶⁰ stabilize receptor
  - Arg/Gly389 polymorphism structural explanation for pharmacological differences
  - 5 detergent molecules (bucindolol), 12 (carvedilol) observed

### DOI 8: 10.1016##J.STR.2014.12.012 — PepTSo (Proton-Coupled Oligopeptide Transporter)
- **New page created**: [[peptso]] — POT family transporter from *S. oneidensis* at 3.0 Å (PDB 4UVM)
  - 12 TM helices, two inverted-topology 6-helix repeats, P4₁2₁2
  - Double scissor-switch gating model: periplasmic gate (H1,H2,H7,H8), cytoplasmic gate (H4,H5,H10,H11)
  - Salt bridges: D136-K439 and K84-D79 stabilize outward-facing
  - Proline kinks in H8 (P345, P353) essential for transport
  - DEER spectroscopy confirms conformational dynamics
  - MD simulations: both proteins sample inward-facing, occluded, outward-facing states

### DOI 9: 10.1016##S0022-2836(03)00024-X — LH2 Light-Harvesting Complex
- **New page created**: [[lh2-rps-acidophila]] — LH2 from *Rps. acidophila* at 2.0 Å (100 K) with TLS refinement
  - C₉ nonameric ring, 18 B850 BChl a (9 dimers), 9 B800 BChl a, 2 rhodopin glucoside per unit
  - TLS refinement: 48 tensors optimal, reveals functionally relevant pigment motions
  - B850-Ueq=0.4 Å², B800-Ueq=0.6 Å², inter-pigment displacements ~0.7 Å
  - Ligands: B850 to α-His31/β-His30, B800 to α-Met1 (carboxy-modified)
  - Detergent: β-octyl glucoside (BOG) in preparation and crystallization
  - Energy transfer implications: TLS motions (3-7 ps) may drive energy transfer

### DOI 10: 10.1016##S0969-2126(99)80118-X — Bacteriorhodopsin at 1.9 Å
- **New page created**: [[bacteriorhodopsin-19a]] — bR from *Halobacterium salinarum* in LCP at 1.9 Å
  - 7 TM helices, retinal bound to Lys216 via Schiff base
  - 8 well-ordered water molecules in proton translocation pathway (Schiff base → Asp85 → Asp212 → Arg82 → Glu194 → Glu204)
  - 9 lipid phytanyl moieties modeled (native purple membrane lipids)
  - MALDI-MS single crystal: PGP-Me, TGD, S-TGA-1, S-TeGa
  - LCP crystallization in monoolein — preserves native lipid environment
  - Cytoplasmic side more flexible than extracellular (B-factors 24-33 vs 19-26 Å²)
  - No ordered waters on cytoplasmic side — hydrophobic seal (Val49-Leu93)

